        <div class="dBoxMain">
            <div class="mainBodyTextTop">
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">re:</div><div class="textLeft1"><span class="fs10">&nbsp; Communion/Lord's Supper/Eucharist, etc </span></div></div>
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">emoticon:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp;<img src="http://acx.prospero.com/dir-app/icon.aspx?realmId=185&iconTypeId=2&iconName=0" border=0 height=15 width=15 align=texttop alt="Emoticon"></span></div></div>
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">message #:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; 975.5 in response to <a href="message.asp?webtag=iv-pplibchrist&msg=975.1" target=_self>975.1</a></span></div></div>


                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">from:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; <a class="memname" href="/dir-app/bbcard/profile.asp?webtag=iv-pplibchrist&uid=369118715" onClick="return LBB(369118715);">ashmama</a> <nobr>&nbsp;<img src="http://acx.prospero.com/dir-app/icon.aspx?realmId=185&iconTypeId=1&iconName=194" border=0 height=15 width=15 align=texttop alt='Member Icon'></nobr></span></div></div>
                
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">to:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; <a class="memname" href="/dir-app/bbcard/profile.asp?webtag=iv-pplibchrist&uid=369381505" onClick="return LBB(369381505);">trudyj</a> <nobr></nobr></span></div></div>
                
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">date:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; 7/15/2003 2:50 pm</span></div></div>
                <div class="oneLine"><div class="boldText">replies:</div><div class="textLeft"><span class="fs11">&nbsp; 5</span></div></div>
            </div><!-- End: mainBodyTextTop -->

            <br clear="all" />

            <div class="mainBodyText">
                <span class="fs5">A resume of Holy Communion in my church:

<P>Age limit: None. If you (and presumably your parents) feel that you're ready, join us. It is God who does the calling. If you want to go, you've been &quot;invited.&quot;

<P>Membership requirement: None. Anyone who feels him/herself to be a part of the body of Christ is welcome.

<P>Frequency: Once a month, on the first Sunday. This seems a bit arbitrary to me, so I suspect it is for practical reasons.

<P>What: Bread and grape juice. The rationale for the juice is that alcohol might be a barrier to some. The bread is usually leavened and often (horrifyingly) something I suspect is Wonder bread. I much prefer the tasteless Episcopalian wafers of my childhood. In the summer, when there are fewer people to serve, each communicant pulls off hunks of wheat bread, an unfortunate practice because sometimes you get a heck of a lot more than a mouthful. The grape juice is served in tiny cups.

<P>Where: At the altar rail, on our knees. We take turns going up in rows.

<P>Whom: The elements are consecrated by our full time male and part-time female pastor, then served by lay people as well as the pastors.

<P>How: We follow the standard &quot;service of word and table II&quot; in the UMC hymnal. 

<P>Comment: I don't really have strong preferences regarding communion, except this one: I believe it should be open to all professing Christians, regardless of their denomination. I am never comfortable in a church where I or my children cannot commune. I also like the practice of serving grape juice instead of wine: no one should be barred from the table of Christ! Besides, I like my Holy Spirit buzz to be distinct from my Sauvignon Blanc buzz! 

<P></span>
                <table><tr></tr></table>
            </div>

